<%# Phase 37 Wave A1 вЂ” `/channels` mocked shell.

    Locked layout (2026-05-19 user вЂ” chip-row consolidation pass):

      channels  [+][-]
      [ ] 7d  [ ] 28d  [ ] 3m  [ ] 365d  [ ] alltime  [ ] <prev_year>  [ ] <current_year>  [ ] <prev_month>  [ ] <current_month>       [ ]| | [ ]| | [ ]| |
      в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ  (hairline)
      <ID-card shelf вЂ” one tile per channel, horizontal scroll>

    Year/month chip values are computed by
    `Formatting::CurrentChannelFilterChips` so the chip set tracks
    today's date instead of hard-coded literals. URL values for the
    year chips are 4-digit year strings; month-chip URL values are the
    lowercase 3-letter abbreviation (`apr`, `may`, ...), display labels
    capitalize via `%b` (`Apr`, `May`, ...).

    Wave A1 ships with the generic `FilterChipComponent` for every
    chip вЂ” the controller doesn't yet read `?windows=`, `?calendar=`,
    or `?channels=`, so the chips toggle URL state harmlessly (same
    UX as /games chips). Live filtering wires up in later A-steps
    once the user signs off on the visuals.

    Mock data lives in `Channels::MockData`. %>

<% calendar_chips = Formatting::CurrentChannelFilterChips.call %>

<%= render(Channels::TitleBarComponent.new) %>

<%# Two-column block: LEFT = single chip row (time windows + dynamic
    year/month chips inline AFTER alltime); RIGHT = avatar shelf.

    Outer flex container baseline-aligns the two columns so the chip
    row and the RIGHT shelf's checkboxes share the same baseline.
    `gap: 16px` between left and right groups matches
    `Games::FilterRowComponent`'s outer left/right gap
    (filter_row_component.html.erb L18). %>
<section class="channels-chrome"
         style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; margin: 6px 0;">
  <div class="channels-chrome__filters"
       style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;">
    <%# Single chip row вЂ” time windows + dynamic year/month chips
        appended after `alltime`. Window chips toggle `?windows=`;
        year+month chips toggle `?calendar=`. Both use csv multi-select. %>
    <div class="channels-filter-row"
         style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; align-items: baseline;">
      <% %w[7d 28d 3m 365d alltime].each do |window| %>
        <%= render(FilterChipComponent.new(
              label: window,
              param: "windows",
              value: window,
              current_params: request.query_parameters,
              csv: true,
              path: "/channels"
            )) %>
      <% end %>
      <% calendar_chips[:years].each do |chip| %>
        <%= render(FilterChipComponent.new(
              label: chip[:label],
              param: "calendar",
              value: chip[:value],
              current_params: request.query_parameters,
              csv: true,
              path: "/channels"
            )) %>
      <% end %>
      <% calendar_chips[:months].each do |chip| %>
        <%= render(FilterChipComponent.new(
              label: chip[:label],
              param: "calendar",
              value: chip[:value],
              current_params: request.query_parameters,
              csv: true,
              path: "/channels"
            )) %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="channels-chrome__avatars">
    <%= render(Channels::AvatarShelfComponent.new(channels: @channels, current_params: request.query_parameters)) %>
  </div>
</section>

<hr class="hairline">

<%# Wave A1 (2026-05-19 chip-row consolidation) main content area вЂ”
    first row is the ID-card shelf (6 cards, one per channel). Uses
    the canonical headless `ShelfComponent` (heading: nil) вЂ” the
    parallel `Channels::IdCardShelfComponent` was removed in the same
    pass. Subsequent A-steps fill the remaining metric sections
    (basics totals, top content, window summaries, audience, traffic,
    heatmap, trends) beneath it inside the same `.channels-main` wrapper.

    2026-05-19 вЂ” each shelf renders a trailing `<hr class="hairline">`
    so the bottom edge of the shelf reads as a clean separator, matching
    the inter-shelf hairline convention used on `/games` (see
    `app/views/games/index.html.erb` lines 158, 173, 180). The
    `ShelfComponent` does NOT emit its own `<hr>` by design (see the
    header comment on `app/components/shelf_component.rb`); views own
    the composition between shelves. %>
<section class="channels-main">
  <%= render(ShelfComponent.new(
        heading: nil,
        extra_classes: "channels-id-card-shelf",
        shelf_kind: "channels-id-cards"
      )) do %>
    <% @channels.each do |channel| %>
      <%= render(Channels::IdCardComponent.new(channel: channel)) %>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>
  <hr class="hairline">
</section>
